From: OrangeFox Recovery Patcher <patch@orangefox.recovery>
Date: Mon, 2 Jun 2026 08:51:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Disable copySqliteDb call to prevent servicemanager hang

The android::keystore::copySqliteDb() function call can cause
servicemanager to hang when crypto is enabled. This function is not
essential for basic crypto functionality and causes more problems
than it solves.

diff --git a/twrp.cpp b/twrp.cpp
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/twrp.cpp
+++ b/twrp.cpp
@@ -249,7 +249,9 @@
 #endif
 
 #ifdef TW_INCLUDE_CRYPTO
-	android::keystore::copySqliteDb();
+	// Disabled to prevent servicemanager deadlock
+	// This call causes servicemanager to wait indefinitely when crypto is enabled
+	// android::keystore::copySqliteDb();
 #endif
 	Decrypt_Page(skip_decryption, datamedia);
 
